ce:section.ce:para:
The solution resistance (Rs
                        ), double-layer capacitance (Cdl
                        ), charge transfer resistance (Rct
                        ), and Warburg impedance (Wo
                        ) of the working electrodes were assessed by EIS to explore the electrocatalytic performance of the electrodes. ANyquist plot or a Bode plot is typically used to depict the results of the interfacial electrochemical properties of the electrodes. TheNyquist plot typicallyhas a semi-circular and linear zone [4,46,57]. While the linear portion depicts the diffusion-limitingprocess at low frequencies, the semi-circle's diameter reveals an estimation of electron transfer resistance at high frequencies [36,58]. According to
                        Fig. 4
                        a Nyquist plot, the Cu0-OGQ/GCE exhibited the smallest semicircle at high frequency with the lowest electron transfer resistance. The semi-circular diameter and Rct
                         dramatically increased following the modification of the bare GCE with OGQ. It is important to note that the Cu0 doping enhanced the electrical conductivity and charge transfer ability of the Cu0-OGQ than that of the OGQ electrode, as seen by the smaller semicircle that the Cu0-OGQ/GCE exhibited when compared to the OGQ/GCE. It implies that the interfacial resistance wasdecreased by the Cu0 dopant.
